cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the distribution of interference power and success probability, which are key concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the downlink of a wireless network and the area spectral efficiency, which are relevant topics in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The use of multiple antennas at base stations and single antennas at mobile stations can be seen as a multiagent system, where the agents (antennas) interact with each other to achieve a common goal (successful communication). 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The spatially correlated fading channels can be seen as a network of channels, where the correlation between channels can affect the overall network performance. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The concept of maximizing the ratio of signal power to interference power can be seen as a game between the transmitter and the interferer, where each player tries to maximize their own payoff (signal power or interference power).
